# My Personal Website

This repository contains the source code for my personal website, built as a simple static site with HTML, CSS, and some JavaScript for interactivity. [page:1]

The live site is deployed via GitHub Pages from the `master` branch. [page:1]

---

## What this site is

My site is a small home on the internet where I introduce myself, showcase my work, and post occasional blogs.  
It is intentionally lightweight so I can focus on learning and experimenting with web fundamentals.

The main page includes sections for **About me**, **Work**, and **Blog**, along with links to my social profiles and email. [page:1]

---

## Features

- A single-page layout with dedicated sections for who I am, what I work on, and what I write about.  
- A typewriter-style animation that reveals headings and paragraphs in sequence. [page:1]  
- Random visual effects like a moving white stripe and colorful title text. [page:1]  
- Direct links to some of my technical projects and blog posts.  
- A footer with quick access to my email, LinkedIn, Instagram, GitHub, and WhatsApp. [page:1]

---

## Repository structure

```text
.
├── index.html        # Main landing page
├── blog/             # Blog posts and related pages
├── work/             # Project and portfolio pages
├── scripts/          # JavaScript for animations and effects
└── README            # This file
```

[page:1]

---

## How I develop locally

There is no build step; I just open `index.html` in a browser or serve it using a simple static HTTP server. [page:1]

Example with Python:

```bash
# Python 3
python -m http.server 8080
# then visit http://localhost:8080
```

---

## How I deploy

I use **GitHub Pages** for deployment: [page:1]

1. I push changes to the `master` branch.
2. GitHub Pages rebuilds and serves the updated version of the site.
3. I visit the configured GitHub Pages URL to verify everything looks correct.

---

## Future plans

I plan to:

- Add more detailed write-ups for my projects under `/work`.  
- Publish more blogs under `/blog`, especially about the things I am learning.  
- Iterate on the design and add more subtle visual touches as my frontend skills improve.

